Self-emulsifying drug delivery systems which belongs to lipid based formulations (LBFs), have shown to improve the slow and incomplete drug dissolution, and facilitate the formation of the highly solubilized phase of drug for enhanced drug absorption. Also, the self-emulsifying formulations can be easily filled in soft and hard gelatin capsules due to their anhydrous nature (
 Pouton, 1985; 
 Strickley, 2004).
